What is Aircraft ACMI Leasing?
Aircraft ACMI (Aircraft, Crew, Maintenance, and Insurance) Leasing, commonly referred to as wet leasing, is a leasing arrangement in which the lessor provides a fully operational aircraft along with qualified flight crew, maintenance services, and insurance coverage to the lessee. This enables airlines, cargo operators, charter companies, and governments to rapidly expand operational capacity while minimizing fleet ownership costs and operational risks.

Modern Aircraft ACMI leasing solutions provide comprehensive services including:

·         Aircraft Provision for passenger and cargo operations

·         Professional Flight Crew and Cabin Crew Services

·         Comprehensive Aircraft Maintenance and Technical Support

·         Insurance Coverage for operational security

·         Regulatory Compliance and Air Operator Certification Support

·         Fleet Flexibility for seasonal demand and network expansion

By offering fully operational aircraft with integrated support services, ACMI leasing enables airlines to improve operational flexibility, reduce capital expenditure, accelerate route launches, optimize fleet utilization, and efficiently respond to changing market conditions.

